✅ Java Tip: Always override equals() and hashCode() when necessary.
Example:
@Override
public boolean equals(Object o) { /*...*/ }
@Override
public int hashCode() { /*...*/ }

2025-07-12.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use const constructors for widgets when possible.
Example:
const myWidget = Text('Hello', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 20));

2025-07-15.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use ListView.builder for efficient large lists.
Example:
ListView.builder(
  itemCount: items.length,
  itemBuilder: (context, index) {
    return Text(items[index]);
  },
);

2025-07-17.content:
✅ Java Tip: Use synchronized blocks for thread safety.
Example:
synchronized(this) {
    // critical section
}

2025-07-18.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use FutureBuilder for async UI rendering.
Example:
FutureBuilder(
  future: fetchData(),
  builder: (context, snapshot) {
    if (snapshot.hasData) return Text(snapshot.data);
    else return CircularProgressIndicator();
  },
);

2025-07-20.content:
✅ Java Tip: Use Collections.sort with custom Comparators.
Example:
Collections.sort(list, (a, b) -> a.length() - b.length());

2025-07-21.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use AnimatedContainer for smooth UI transitions.
Example:
AnimatedContainer(
  duration: Duration(seconds: 1),
  width: isLarge ? 200 : 100,
);

2025-07-23.content:
✅ Java Tip: Use Executors for thread pool management.
Example:
ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(3);
executor.execute(() -> System.out.println("Task executed"));

2025-07-24.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use Provider for simple state management.
Example:
Provider.of<Counter>(context).increment();

2025-07-26.content:
✅ Java Tip: Use AtomicInteger for lock-free thread-safe counters.
Example:
AtomicInteger count = new AtomicInteger(0);
count.incrementAndGet();

2025-07-27.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use GestureDetector to handle touch events.
Example:
GestureDetector(
  onTap: () => print("Tapped!"),
  child: Container(color: Colors.blue),
);

2025-07-28.content:
✅ Python Tip: Use functools.lru_cache for memoization.
Example:
from functools import lru_cache
@lru_cache(maxsize=None)
def fib(n):
    return n if n < 2 else fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)

2025-07-29.content:
✅ Java Tip: Use lambda expressions for cleaner code.
Example:
list.forEach(item -> System.out.println(item));

2025-07-30.content:
✅ Flutter/Dart Tip: Use LayoutBuilder for responsive widget sizing.
Example:
LayoutBuilder(
  builder: (context, constraints) {
    return Text("Max Width: ${constraints.maxWidth}");
  },
